In a pre-tender advertisement in the Official Journal of the European Union on 24 September 2010, Transport Scotland says it is looking for a contractor to develop and support ICT for the Scottish Integrated Roads Information System (Siris).On 2 August 2010, the agency became responsible for trunk roads and the contract will also be expected to deliver annual road condition surveys of Scotland's trunk road network.If it goes ahead, the deal will run from 2011.